Advanced Rule-Based Approaches for Explainable Sentiment Analysis (for Czech)

immm00@vse.cz

Repository for diploma thesis files. 

rule_based.ipynb - main notebook with rule_based approach
Keras_DNN.ipynb	 - DNN implementation example
Keras_DNN_cross_val.ipynb - DNN implementation used for cross-validation
ml-extracted.ipynb - SVM and Max Entropy for extracted dataset
ml-synthetic.ipynb - SVM and Max Entropy for synthetic dataset
articles - scraped articles
datasets - datasets used in the notebooks
text_resources - lexicons, shifters and others

Contains datasets from HABERNAL, Ivan, PTÁČEK, Tomáš and STEINBERGER, Josef, 2013-06. Sentiment Analy-
sis in Czech Social Media Using Supervised Machine Learning. In: BALAHUR, Alexandra,
GOOT, Erik van der and MONTOYO, Andres (eds.). Proceedings of the 4th Workshop
on Computational Approaches to Subjectivity, Sentiment and Social Media Analysis. At-
lanta, Georgia: Association for Computational Linguistics, pp. 65–74. Available also from:
https://aclanthology.org/W13-1609. Original source is https://corpora.kiv.zcu.cz/sentiment/.